  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence was gathered through a prospective observational registry study in which pump effluent hemolysis indices were recorded across clinical operating conditions; this dataset is cited throughout the validation narrative as providing controlled-experiment-grade corroboration of the CFD predictions, given the breadth of flow-speed combinations captured and the rigorous instrumentation protocols applied.",
