    "type": "Requirement",
    "name": "Hemolysis validation verification method requirement",
    "description": "Per the device submission plan and ASME V&V 40 Section 6.4, validation of CFD-predicted hemolysis indices against physical measurements shall be performed using a controlled experiment in which flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid properties are independently manipulated under laboratory conditions to isolate causal relationships. This ensures that confounding clinical variables do not obscure the model-to-measurement agreement assessment.",
    "requiredVerificationMethod": "controlled-experiment"
  },
  "hasActivity": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cpb-hemolysis-validation-study",
    "type": "Activity",
    "name": "CPB hemolysis prospective observational registry study",
    "description": "A prospective observational registry study was conducted across three clinical sites, enrolling 47 CPB procedures. Hemolysis indices (plasma-free hemoglobin, relative hemolysis index) were measured at standardized time intervals. Operating conditions—flow rate (2.0–5.5 L/min) and pump speed (1800–3200 RPM)—were recorded as set by the perfusionist in routine clinical practice. The resulting dataset spans all five flow-speed combinations of interest and provides a comprehensive empirical basis for comparison with CFD predictions. Instrumentation calibration records and inter-site harmonization protocols were applied to ensure measurement consistency, lending the dataset a rigor comparable to laboratory benchmarks.",
    "activityType": "observational-study"
  },
