      "description": "Plasma-free hemoglobin (PfHb) temporal trends predicted by the CFD hemolysis model were compared against registry-measured PfHb at 30-minute intervals. Trend agreement (Pearson r = 0.91, p < 0.001) across the 47 cases supports the model's ability to capture hemolysis dynamics. The observational dataset, while gathered in routine clinical settings, covered the full operating envelope specified in the COU and was treated by the assessment team as providing controlled-experiment-equivalent coverage due to the breadth and instrumentation quality of the data collected.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cpb-hemolysis-validation-study",
